    "body": "### Problem\n\nCalling `nvim_input_mouse()` right after `nvim_open_win()` with coordinates inside new floating window does not focus the floating window.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Create config file with the following content:\r\n```lua\r\n_G.test_mouse = function()\r\n  local buf_id = vim.api.nvim_create_buf(false, true)\r\n  local config = { relative = 'editor', row = 1, col = 1, height = 10, width = 10 }\r\n  vim.api.nvim_open_win(buf_id, false, config)\r\n\r\n  vim.api.nvim_input_mouse('left', 'press', '', 0, 5, 5)\r\nend\r\n```\r\n2. Open `nvim` with that config.\r\n3. Execute `:lua _G.test_mouse()`. Floating window is not focused, although it was \"clicked\" on.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nFloating window should be focused, as it is on `ebe489d` commit.\r\n\r\n------\r\n\r\nThe #25629 seems to be the reason. Applying the following patch fixes this issue:\r\n\r\n```patch\r\ndiff --git a/src/nvim/getchar.c b/src/nvim/getchar.c\r\nindex 5f3b14399..46a786c1d 100644\r\n--- a/src/nvim/getchar.c\r\n+++ b/src/nvim/getchar.c\r\n@@ -2862,9 +2862,7 @@ int inchar(uint8_t *buf, int maxlen, long wait_time)\r\n\r\n     // Always flush the output characters when getting input characters\r\n     // from the user and not just peeking.\r\n-    if (wait_time == -1L || wait_time > 10L) {\r\n-      ui_flush();\r\n-    }\r\n+    ui_flush();\r\n\r\n     // Fill up to a third of the buffer, because each character may be\r\n     // tripled below.\r\n```\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.10.0-dev-bf70a33\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nNo (doesn't have this functionality)\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nEndeavourOS Linux x86_64 (6.5.6-arch1-1)\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nst-0.9\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nst-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nappimage",
